			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To those that say beastlords would mind mages having a pet heal as efficient as ours ought to go look at the thread Xalmat made about pet heals.  Many beastlords flat out state we would not mind if mages got pet heals equal to ours.  A lot flat out say we would gladly trade our long casting heal with no recast delay for your fast heal with a recasting delay.
<br />

<br />
Our long casting heal stops us from doing melee or spell DPS.  Our warder also has a good deal less hp then you’re tanking type pets (earth and possible air?).  Our warders also have less avoidance and less mitigation.
<br />

<br />
I have read that many mages will chain two heals for your pets but the quick casting heals and recast delay I think might allow a mage the chance to slip in a nuke.  A beastlord is often better just casting a few heals on himself and stepping back in to tank.
<br />

<br />
The way I look at it we have a big slow heal for a pet with less hp that takes damage faster.  Mages have a faster casting heal that almost forces them to go back burning down a mob.  Beastlords have slow that allows us to take less hits but since we are more defensive in nature we spend more time taking down a mob.
<br />

<br />
In the end it seems Sony believes mages are supposed to get fast heals with long recast while beast get slow heals with no recast.  The issue may lie in convincing Sony have to make them “equivalent”  I think they should be buy making them equivalent is probably still up for debate to many people. =P
<br />

<br />
Kat<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=540316" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.designsbyeve.com/myimages/katonissiggy.jpg" border="0" /></a>
