<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/eusa_wall.gif" alt="Brick wall" border="0" /> either make the heals WORTH memming or make the pets so that we can chain nuke and kill the mob without the mob shredding the pet. my DPoC RS with virt, BO5 can take a mob in tactics no prob </span><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">IF THE MOB IS BEING SLOWED</span></span></span>. If i try the same thing in BoT<span style="font-size: 7px; line-height: normal">rains</span>/HoH<span style="font-size: 7px; line-height: normal">ell</span> or even Valor<span style="font-size: 7px; line-height: normal">-less players </span>or storms<span style="font-size: 7px; line-height: normal"> of idiots </span>i get shredded by the mob regardless of healing or nuking.<img src="images/smiles/eusa_pray.gif" alt="Pray" border="0" /></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
If you are using a DPoC Rathe's Son with Virt in the Plane of Valor and your pet is getting "shredded" then you're doing something wrong or you aren't being completely honest.  Your fellow mages (including Xalmat) have posted on these boards that it's perfectly possible for mages to "pet tank" in Valor with DPoC pets, using heals.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Valor is a tier 2 zone. 
<br />

<br />
HoH and BoT (tier 3) are quite bit harder and are not DPOC focused earth pet or air pet soloable and can only be done by earth pet yoyo kiting (provided the mobs don't summon).
<br />

<br />
On the other hand if the mobs are slowed they can be off tanked in a traditional pet acting as MT and mage nuking from a ranged position. 
<br />

<br />
Currently the heals are so slow that they have to be chaincast together (1200Hp and 900Hp heals) and the pet does not have enough DPS or regen to survive the encounter. The mage gets into a endless loop of healing the pet and the overall pet HP decreases with every cast until the pet is dead and then the mage either gates, flees or dies.  
<br />

<br />
Now if mage pet heals were improved, it would provide the mage with the ability to toss in a nuke once and a while to kill the mob.
<br />

<br />
This whole issue is not the mages against the beastlords or vice versa. It's about being able to survive in an off tanking situation.  There are many many times even in groups where the mage is offtanking and the slowers and healers are not giving the pet anywhere near the attention of the MT. 
<br />

<br />
A mage relies totally on its pet for defense.  Mages can't heal the pet well enough to prevent it from dying in the event that the group is too busy keeping the MT up. 
<br />

<br />
Mages can't off tank the mob themselves to take aggro away from their pet in order to save the pet from dying. Mages cant slow the mob to reduce the pet's damage.
<br />

<br />
The way our pet heals work today we CAN'T sneak in a nuke in between chain casts to gain the advantage and defeat the mob in these zones.
<br />

<br />
At tier 3 and beyond we have reached the "point of diminishing returns" on pet HP thru our heals. The pet dies and the mage is defeated.
<br />

<br />
That is why mages need to have strong pets and pet buffs.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=639739" target="_blank" class="postlink">Danille Impholder</a>
<br />
Ayonae Ro ~ Keep Norrath Safe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
