			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">"--Magicians are a very focused class, sacrificing some diversity for power in their area of expertise."
<br />

<br />
Beastlords are blown away by mages in terms of DPS.   What beasts sacrifice in terms of power they gain in versatility (giving them a different type of power).
<br />

<br />
Necros also blow away beastlords in terms of dps, for this they sacrifice the strength of their pet as a tank.  Necromancers also have versatility, far more than a beastlord I would venture to say.
<br />

<br />
Beastlords are the defensive end of the pet spectrum, mages are the offensive end, and I would venture to say that necros are the versatility powerhouse.  
<br />

<br />
Why are beastlords heals being attacked?  I have absolutely no problem with giving mages the same efficiency heals as beastlords.  It just seems silly that the focus is on a comparison to another class rather than to the mob.<br />_________________<br />Dysz Iblamethoss
<br />
Feral Lord of Rest in Peace, Ayonae Ro</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
